'''Kaichi Hirate''' was a Japanese soldier. He was a Captain in the [[Japanese Imperial Army]] and during [[World War II]] was Camp Commander of the First Branch Camp at [[Hakkokate]]. In 1946, charged with mistreatment of [[prisoners of war]], he was tried by the [[International Military Tribunal for the Far East]] at [[Yokohama]]. He was found guilty, sentenced to death, and hanged.<ref>Stella Lee Researcher, U.C. Berkeley War Crimes Studies Center, [http://wcsc.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/Japan/Yokohama/Reviews/Yokohama_Review_Hirate.htm], "Case Synopses From Judge Advocate's Reviews: Yokohama Class B and C War Crimes Trials," 2007.</ref>

