{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} '''Lady Mary Butler''' (1689 – 2 January 1713) was the second daughter of the [[James Butler, 2nd Duke of Ormonde|2nd Duke of Ormonde]] and maternally a granddaughter of the [[Henry Somerset, 1st Duke of Beaufort|1st Duke of Beaufort]]. She was born at [[Kilkenny Castle]] in [[Ireland]]. She married [[John Ashburnham, 1st Earl of Ashburnham|John, 3rd Baron Ashburnham]], on 21 October 1710, and died two years later in childbirth. She was [[Jonathan Swift]]’s "greatest favourite"; he wrote "I am in excessive concern for her death, I hardly knew a more valuable person on all accounts."
