'''Æthelwine''' (or '''Ethelwine''' or '''Aethelwine''') was an [[Anglo-Saxons|Anglo-Saxon]] [[Bishop of Wells]]. He was consecrated 1013, and was expelled to make way for [[Brihtwine]], but was restored and then once more expelled. He died possibly around 1027.<ref name=Handbook222>Fryde, et al. ''Handbook of British Chronology'' p. 222</ref>

